node.text:
@natashanic 💐 ❤️ 

VD: A series of clips of @natashanic ‘s mom putting on roller skates. You can hear laughing cheering and a bit of conversation muffled in the background as music plays over the video. The mom and daughter duo is skating around on a blue ramp doing standing tricks and poses together while helping one another with a hand. The mom tries out skating on the ramp transition and then at the end taking her skates off. There are white captions over the video that read “” when your mom puts on skates... for the first time in years...many years. And She doesn’t even skip a beat! She even teaches you a trick or two...she takes a run on the mini! Yup still got it! Happy Mother’s Day!

node.text:
In today's video, @kianayouwanna announces the winners of February & March Moxi Skate Daily winners as well as some updates to the challenge. It has been such a wonderful time to watch everyone participate in this & see everyones progressions, passion, the friendships they have built & so much more that comes with Moxi Skate Daily. What has been your favorite parts about participating in this challenge so far? Tell us in the comments below! 

Winners from February: 
Instagram: @sk8.bagel
TikTok: Mandimortem 

Winners from March: 
Instagram: @veebeerollin
Tiktok: Toestops

We have a few updates: To participate every month in the prizes specifically we will be picking 1 winner from each TikTok & Instagram & picking from the hashtag of #202funday30 to choose these winners. There will be two winners every month. We will check to make sure that you have been skating at least 30 days so make sure you use the hashtags & post your videos on a feed. Unfortunately we can not track them if they are only in your stories. 

With feedback from the community we can understand that it is not accessible for all to skate every day. We have adjusted the rules on how to enter for prizes by allowing you to start whenever you would like, but to participate you must enter by skating at least 30 days this year, post about it while using the hashtag #202funday#1, #202funday#2 etc etc until 202funday30 and on! (This was a required # from the beginning) and #moxiskatedaily 

 We encourage you to keep on continuing the days that you skate because it is amazing to see how many days you can skate in the year & the progression that you accomplish in doing so! We will still be awarding a winner for the full year once we end 2021! So we encourage you to keep going until  #202funday365 ! We will throw in some extra fun prizes for bigger milestones, any inspirations that we see in the skate world or just for fun they just won’t be every month. So we encourage you to continue to skate! 

Check back at the beginning of May to find out the Winners for April!

Video description in the comments!

#MoxiSkateDaily #202funday30

#MOXISKATEDAILY is the original 365 Days of Skate Challenge 

The challenge is extremely rewarding, positive, motivating and creates harmony and excitement in our community through participation. 

Participants stay connected throughout the year by virtually encouraging daily roller skating through video posts AND we meet lots of friends while doing it!

While following along in the contest by checking the hashtags we become inspired by the improving skaters that seem to blossom like beautiful flowers throughout the year! 

Here are the rules!

1. Roller Skate every single day and take a video or make an edit of video clips taken from the same day 

2. Post your daily video from that day to your Instagram OR TikTok feed, or both. 

3.  In the description of the video post, use #MOXISKATEDAILY and also #202FUNday1 to represent the corresponding day you are  on 

For example.... on your first day, January 1st, you will use #202FUNday1 and on Day 2 you will use #202FUNday2 and on Day 180.you will use #202FUNday180

4. You must be wearing and moving on your roller skates in your video post

5.  To win the GRAND PRIZE you must start January 1st, even if you are waiting for skates. For milestone winners, you can start on any day. So long as you are participating, you can win a prize throughout the year on a milestone day. Milestone days are not limited to 30 days, 60 days, 90 days and 180 days. There may be random milestone days, so KEEP SKATING! 

On milestone days throughout the year we will be giving away Camp Tickets, Pairs of Roller Skates and limited edition items to participants and on the last day we award a GRAND PRIZE (to a random winner who posted every single for day for 356 days). 

Our only ask is that you DO NOT CHEAT by stacking clips and posting later while using the hashtags. 

We hope this contest brings a momentous motivation that will IMPROVE YOUR SKATING and get you. STOKED ON YOUR PROGRESS and INSPIRED BY THE PROGRESS OF OTHERS and to CONNECT YOU TO THE ROLLER SKATING COMMUNITY! 

Thank you again for all of your patience, support, open mindedness and well wishes. 

We wish you the very best this NEW YEAR's HOLIDAY!

Sometimes as skaters and soon to be skaters, it’s hard to find the information we need. We slide into each other’s dms and email customer service, but that’s just not enough! Sometimes, we just need someone to talk to....

Well, everyone at Moxi is here to help and you will be helping Moxi to employ skaters with a special service we are offering! 

Next month you’ll be able to book a session with a skater that’s been trained in hardware, boots, skate set ups and maintenence of your roller skates! Even if we don’t have skates, we’ll give you advice on your dream set up so you know what to get elsewhere. We want you to be educated on what you need to stay rolling or get rolling! 

Reserve a one on one 20min call with a skater for $20. They can help you with recommendations from the tip of your toe stop to the top of your helmet! Link in bio to book yours!

#moxivirtualskateshop #virtualskateshop #moxirollerskates #shopwithaskater @fat_girl_has_moxi

node.title: Too many people out there are needing an inspiring roll model rn!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by MOXI ROLLER SKATES on August 09, 2021 tagging @_legs_. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
Whats the best combo to skate in? Comfy rompers & skater socks to match, of course!  Ready to Roll Rompers are out now and available in four fantastic colors: Sky Blue, Black, Clementine & Lilac! We made these rompers just a little bit longer to cover your backside so you can feel comfortable wearing them literally anywhere!

Also out now is our new Moxi 19 inch skater socks available in five new color ways & now the perfect length to show off some color below the knee! Get ready to roll in style!

Get your outfit of the season over at Moxiskates.com

ID: An image of Legs (she/her) skating fakie on a black and white Dalmatian spotted half pipe. Legs is a white women with light tan skin and long brown hair with bangs. She is mid trick on the ramp holding her right leg with her right hand behind her & smiling. She is wearing pink sunnies on her head, a Lilac spaghetti strap romper, white socks with light pink & dark pink horizontal stripes at the top & Lilac Moxi Lolly skates. The background includes the Dalmatian ramp she is skating on, a brown back yard fence, bamboo behind the fence & a blue sky. 
#MoxiRomper #Romper #SkaterSocks

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by MOXI ROLLER SKATES on August 09, 2021 tagging @sssagan.

node.text:
Our Brightest Rainbow Hoodie comes in handy for those early morning or evening skate sessions to keep you warm & keep a positive mindset! No matter the situation things will get brighter after the storm goes away & as long as you can skate we say it helps the storm move faster! 🛼❤️

Let our Brightest Rainbow Hoodie cheer you up at moxiskates.com 

ID: A close up image of Sagan(she/her) wearing a black  Brightest Rainbow hoodie & gold Shells Bells pants. The graphic on the hoodie has a red, orange red & yellow rainbow circle with a yellow Rainbow Rider roller skate on the bottom middle. In the middle of the circle is text in white & cursive that reads "The Brightest Rainbows Follow the Darkest Storms". Behind her is the Moxi ice cream truck which is patterned brown & light pink leopard spots. 

#MoxiSweater #RainbowSweater

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by MOXI ROLLER SKATES on August 09, 2021. May be an image of footwear.

node.text:
Let sunshine & rainbows follow you wherever you go! 🛼☀️🌈

📸: @fayonwheels

ID: An image of yellow rainbow roller skates with orange toe stops & blue wheels. The Roller skates have a black heel, a black "M' on the side of the high ankle & a red, orange & blue rainbow from the heel to the middle of the boot. 

#yellowSunshineRainbowRiders #RainbowRiders #RainbowRollerskates

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by MOXI ROLLER SKATES on August 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Brightesi The Rainbows Follow Darkest The Storms'.

node.text:
"The brightest rainbows follow the darkest storms" is a quote to remember! In times where things seem dark let the Brightest Rainbow hoodie give you a reminder that dark days will always get brighter.

Hoodie is now on sale at moxiskates.com 🛼🌈

ID: An image of a graphic on a Black hoodie. The graphic has a red, orange red & yellow rainbow circle with a yellow Rainbow Rider roller skate on the bottom middle. In the middle of the circle is text in white & cursive that reads "The Brightest Rainbows Follow the Darkest Storms".

ID2: An image of @sssagan (she/her) who is wearing the Brightest Rainbow hoodie & gold Shells Bells. Sagan is a white women with shoulder length orange ombre hair. Behind her is the Moxi ice cream truck which is patterned brown & light pink leopard spots. You can see the start of a light pink "M" on the right side of the truck.

#RainbowHoodie #MoxiHoodie #rollerskate #moxirollerskates #moxiskates #liferolls

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by MOXI ROLLER SKATES on August 09, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Brightesi The Rainbows Follow Darkest The Storms'.
Photo shared by MOXI ROLLER SKATES on August 09, 2021 tagging @sssagan. May be an image of 1 person and standing.
Photo shared by MOXI ROLLER SKATES on August 08, 2021 tagging @m._.rph. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
Cats got your Fundae wheels? You better surrender them! With a face like that we wouldn't want to take them away! 

PC: @m._.rph 

ID: An image of a grey and white striped cat who is laying on a brown wooden floor with one paw on a pair of packaged blue roller skate wheels. There is another pack of 4 pink wheels on the floor as well and you can see a white, black and brown rug in the corner left of the image. 

#FundaeWheels #MoxiWheels #MoxiRollerSkateWheels #RollerSkateWheels #HybridRollerSkatesWheel

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by MOXI ROLLER SKATES on August 08, 2021 tagging @justabrazilianroller. May be an image of footwear.

node.text:
@justabrazilianroller just got her order & it looks like someone is lurking in the background! Not to worry that's just her cat Charles Darwin checking on the awesome Moxi products she just got! New Jack boots & laces! We love to see it! 

If you need some new roller skate boots we have some sizes left in Lilac, Clementine & Floss on moxiskates.com! 

ID: An Image of a box sitting on a table with a patterned rug on top of it. In the box is Jade jack boots with original lining, Moxi Stickers, a Moxi card & white laces. On the right corner behind the box is the head of a white & brown kitten peaking around it. The background is brick walling. 

#MoxiJackSkates #MoxiJackBoots #RollerSkatesAndCats #MoxiCats #RollerSkateBoot #MoxiCats

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by MOXI ROLLER SKATES on August 08, 2021 tagging @rollergoolie.

node.text:
It's international cat day & we couldn't help, but share! Here is Karli's cat Loui being as cute as ever! If you have a cat give it a pet from Moxi! 

ID: An image of a grey cat sitting in green grass with dandelions next to Karli's feet who is wearing scuffed up roller skates with yellow laces & white & blue socks. 

#MoxiCats

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by MOXI ROLLER SKATES on August 07, 2021 tagging @erikawheelsnwaves. May be an image of one or more people.

node.text:
It's a beautiful summer! ☀️ Let's spend it outside skating! Moxi pads are for all wheels so don't be shy to wear them however you roll!

Let’s skate together with the protection of Moxi Pads! In stock on moxiskates.com

ID: An image of Erika from the chest down holding a skateboard in one hand. Erika has tan skin and is wearing a blue short sleeved tee, blue denim shorts, Pink Moxi knee pads, wrist guards, white shoes and in their right hand is holding a grey long board. Behind them is a grey pool bowl. Behind the bowl you can see green trees. 

#MoxiPads #SkatePads

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by MOXI ROLLER SKATES on August 07, 2021 tagging @cuttincandy187. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
Moxi Pads come with a contoured form-fitting design that cradles the knee & has a superior foam system that absorbs hard impacts! Perfect for all types of skating since it'll keep you protected & mobile. 

Moxi pads come in Jade, Pink, Lavender & the newst addition the Wild Pack! You can grab a set now at moxiskates.com 

ID: An image of @cuttincandy187 (she/her) who is a Swedish roller skater with white skin and golden long hair. She is sitting with one knee on the ground, one elbow resting on the bended knee, and one finger is touching her mouth. She is smiling. She is wearing dark sunglasses, a white tight top and a short peach-pink skirt, white knee socks, a turquoise set of protection- Moxi knee pads, wrist guards, a S1 helmet and poppy red Moxi Lollys. She is located on a grey cycle track with green forest all around. A glimpse of a turquoise bicycle is showing in the background. 

#MoxiPads #MoxiPadsJade #RollerSkatePads

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by MOXI ROLLER SKATES on August 07, 2021 tagging @fizzleicious. May be an image of 1 person, standing and outdoors.

node.text:
We love to see smiles! That's means you are having fun! What better way to have fun roller skating than to do it where you feel safe & confident! 

Moxi Pads are available in 4 different colors/styles for you to feel confident in!

 You can grab some at moxiskates.com 🛼

ID: Jazzmin (she/her) posing with her new pineapple Lolly skates. Jazzmin is a thin Black and Puerto Rican Woman with dark skin and her hair in a natural Afro puff.
She is wearing a black tank top crop, light blue jean shorts, Pineapple Lollys and Lavender Moxi pads. The background is a dark grey parking lot and a park with a basketball court and nature. 

#MoxiPads #RollerSkateGear #RollerSkatePads #SkatePads

What do we got in stock? 7 cute pairs of Moxi Sunnies for every flavor of the week! 

Grab a pair or two that match your vibe over moxiskates.com! 

VD: A reel video of @evelyn.ivyy (she/her) who is a Latina roller skater with medium skin & brown hair with bangs. She is sitting on a couch and changing the Moxi Sunnies on her face. She changes through all the different kinds of sunnies Moxi owns to show off what is in stock. 
Evelyn is wearing an orange Moxi mask, a black shirt with white collar and an image of a grocery car that has the text “legalize skating in the grocery store”.

#SummerSunnies #HeartShapedSunglasses #SummerItem #MoxiSunnies #CuteShades

node.text:
At Moxi we like to stand out! Our Heart shaped sunnies were made for us to do just that! From the bright pink of Cotton Candy, the sweet rainbow in Snow Cone or the pop of colors in Sprinkle Town. Whatever style you got, sunnies will be sure to make you pop! 

Stay stylish & protected form the sun ☀️🌈

PC: @snoopa 

ID: An image of 3 pairs of heart shaped sunglasses laying on a rainbow knit sweater. The first pair is Rainbow framed with a red tint. The second pair has a clear frame with dots of color and a rainbow tint. The third pair are pink frames with a red to blue fade tint. 

#SummerSunnies #RainbowSunglasses #MoxiSunnies
